<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25118i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25118i">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25118i"> 118(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">A</font> mixes ashes of / letter with tea</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Obviously, it is but a step from listening to the charm-working words of sacred texts to swallowing them; hence the Chinese practice of <mark>burning papers on which charms are written and mixing the ashes with tea</mark>; and the Moslem practice of washing off a verse of the Koran and drinking the water. <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 224</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14073a" href="c14all.htm#c14073a">VI.C.14:073(a)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
